The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Srinagar, Sept. 9 (PTI): Three army soldiers were killed and five injured in an explosion in their vehicle at Pattan in north Kashmirs Baramulla district.           
	The vehicle was part of a convoy. Defence spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel J.S. Brar said investigations were on to find out whether it was a militant attack.           
	We are trying to ascertain what actually happened. Investigations have been launched into this incident, he said.           Srinagar, a 55-year-old man died after a stone hurled by an unidentified person hit him while he was travelling in a vehicle. Ghulam Mohammed Guroo was travelling with his brothers when he was hit by the stone.                   
	Kottayam (PTI): The syndicate of Mahatma Gandhi University has asked the management of the church-run Newman College at Thodupuzha to reconsider its decision to sack lecturer T.J. Joseph.          
	After a meeting of the syndicate, vice-chancellor Rajan Gurukkal said the university forum was of the view that the management did not follow due procedures while dismissing Joseph.           
	Josephs right palm was slashed by activists of a radical outfit for allegedly hurting religious sentiments. The lecturer, who had been served a dismissal notice on September 4, had sent a letter to the college to be reinstated on humanitarian grounds.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): Bombay High Court has directed the trustees of SES English Medium School in Nasik to pay salary arrears according to the Fifth Pay Commission Report to teachers and file a compliance report by the month-end, failing which they would have to face imprisonment. The court has directed the state government to de-recognise the school if the management did not pay up.                  
	 Erode (PTI): Four persons, hailing from Bihar, were arrested on Wednesday on charges of placing huge boulders on the railway tracks in Pungambadi near here, Tamil Nadu police said.
                                                                                                                                              
